  <front>
   <head>CLOE HUNTING.</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="couplet">
     <l n="1" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">her Neck her comely Tresses ty'd,</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Her Iv'ry Quiver graceful by her Side,</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">A-Hunting  went: She lost her Way,</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">And thro' the Woods uncertain chanc'd to stray.</l>
     <l n="5" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">passing by beheld the Maid;</l>
     <l n="6" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">And, Sister Dear, bright  turn, He said:</l>
     <l n="7" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">The hunted Hind lyes close in yonder Brake.</l>
     <l n="8" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Loud  laugh'd, to see the God's Mistake;</l>
     <l n="9" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">And laughing cry'd, Learn better, great Divine,</l>
     <l n="10" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">To know Thy Kindred, and to honour Mine.</l>
     <l n="11" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Rightly advis'd, far hence Thy Sister seek,</l>
     <l n="12" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Or on  Bank, or Peak.</l>
     <l n="13" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">But in This Nymph, My Friend, My Sister know:</l>
     <l n="14" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">She draws My Arrows, and She bends My Bow:</l>
     <l n="15" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Fair  She haunts, and ev'ry neighb'ring Grove</l>
     <l n="16" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Sacred to soft Recess, and gentle Love.</l>
     <l n="17" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Go, with Thy , hurl the pointed Spear</l>
     <l n="18" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">At the rough Boar; or chace the flying Deer:</l>
     <l n="19" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">I and My  take a nobler Aim:</l>
     <l n="20" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">At human Hearts We fling, nor ever miss the Game.</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
